1. OSI and TCP/IP Models
	•	OSI Model (7 Layers):
        •	Layer 1: Physical – Cables, fiber optics, wireless signals.
        •	Layer 2: Data Link – MAC addresses, Ethernet, ARP, VLANs.
        •	Layer 3: Network – IP addressing, routing, NAT.
        •	Layer 4: Transport – TCP vs. UDP, port numbers.
        •	Layer 5: Session – Establishing, managing, terminating sessions.
        •	Layer 6: Presentation – Data formats, encryption.
        •	Layer 7: Application – HTTP, FTP, DNS, SMTP.
	•	TCP/IP Model (4 Layers):
        •	Network Access (Physical + Data Link)
        •	Internet (Network Layer)
        •	Transport (TCP/UDP)
        •	Application (Application, Presentation, Session)

⸻

2. Network Protocols and Security
	•	IP Addressing (IPv4 vs. IPv6)
	•	Common Protocols:
        •	Secure (HTTPS, TLS, IPsec, SSH)
        •	Insecure (HTTP, FTP, Telnet)
	•	Port Security:
        •	Well-Known Ports (0-1023)
        •	Registered Ports (1024-49151)
        •	Dynamic/Ephemeral Ports (49152-65535)

⸻

3. Network Security Controls
	•	Firewalls:
        •	Packet Filtering (Stateless)
        •	Stateful Inspection
        •	Proxy Firewalls
        •	Next-Gen Firewalls (NGFW)
	•	Intrusion Detection and Prevention Systems (IDS/IPS)
	•	Network Access Control (NAC)
	•	Network Segmentation (VLANs, DMZs, Air-Gapping)
	•	DDoS Protection (Rate Limiting, Blackholing, CDNs)

⸻

4. Wireless Network Security
	•	Wi-Fi Security Standards:
        •	WPA2, WPA3
        •	WEP (Weak, avoid using)
	•	Wireless Attacks:
        •	Evil Twin, Rogue APs, Deauthentication Attacks
        •	WPS Bruteforce Attacks
	•	Mitigations:
	•	 Disable WPS, Use Strong WPA3 Encryption, MAC Filtering

⸻

5. Secure Network Design and Architecture
	•	Zero Trust Architecture (ZTA)
	•	Defense in Depth for Networks
	•	Software-Defined Networking (SDN)
	•	Microsegmentation

⸻

6. Voice over IP (VoIP) Security
	•	Threats:
	•	 Eavesdropping, Man-in-the-Middle (MitM), DoS Attacks
	•	Security Measures:
	•	 Encryption (SRTP), Secure SIP, VLANs for VoIP

⸻

7. VPNs and Remote Access Security
	•	VPN Types:
        •	IPsec VPNs (Tunnel vs. Transport Mode)
        •	SSL/TLS VPNs (For Web-Based Access)
        •	L2TP, PPTP (Legacy, Insecure)
	•	Zero Trust Network Access (ZTNA) vs. Traditional VPNs

⸻

8. Network Attacks and Countermeasures
	•	Common Attacks:
        •	Man-in-the-Middle (MitM)
        •	DNS Spoofing / Poisoning
        •	ARP Spoofing
        •	SYN Flood, Smurf Attack
        •	Ransomware Propagation via Network
	•	Mitigation Strategies:
	•	 Strong Encryption, Secure DNS (DNSSEC), Network Monitoring

⸻

9. Content Filtering and Secure Web Gateways
	•	URL Filtering, Sandboxing
	•	Data Loss Prevention (DLP) for Networks

⸻

10. Cloud and Virtual Network Security
	•	Cloud Network Models (Hybrid, Public, Private)
	•	Security Groups, Network ACLs in Cloud
	•	CASB (Cloud Access Security Broker)